# API and Data Rules

- Keep API response shape/status stable unless change is explicitly requested.
- Validate inputs at boundaries and return actionable errors.
- Prefer parameterized queries; justify any unsafe query usage.
- For schema changes, include migration and rollback notes.

# Upgrade Discipline

- Split framework/runtime upgrades from ORM/schema upgrades when possible.
- Record compatibility issues and temporary exceptions in docs.
- Treat schema drift as explicit technical debt with an owner and next action.

# Verification

- Build passes after API/data changes.
- Critical CRUD routes are smoke-tested.
- Known caveats are documented in architecture/README notes.
